Although the longest criminal trial in history is over, a baffling array of civil suits may  follow the McMartin Pre-School molestation case.
One defendant is suing her accusers  and her son may follow suit.
Parents may file suits on behalf of their children, because  the burden of proof is less in a civil litigation.
No decisions have yet been made and  there are doubts that any money would be available if anyone should win.
Two related  cases are underway.
In one, early defendants are suing those who broke the story and, in  another, defendants and the pre-school are suing liability insurance carriers. 
